### 8B. List Virtualization

**Install**: `npm install @tanstack/react-virtual`

**Apply to lists with >50 items**:
- `SearchableSelect` / `SearchableMultiSelect` — dropdown options (can have 200+ items)
- `AccessControlList` — user/role lists
- `AuditLogList` — high-volume log entries
- `CustomerRequestManagementHub` — case lists
- `ContractList`, `InvoiceList` — entity lists

**Pattern**:
```typescript
import { useVirtualizer } from '@tanstack/react-virtual';

function VirtualizedList({ items }: { items: any[] }) {
  const parentRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
  const virtualizer = useVirtualizer({
    count: items.length,
    getScrollElement: () => parentRef.current,
    estimateSize: () => 48, // row height
    overscan: 5,
  });

  return (
    <div ref={parentRef} style={{ height: '400px', overflow: 'auto' }}>
      <div style={{ height: `${virtualizer.getTotalSize()}px`, position: 'relative' }}>
        {virtualizer.getVirtualItems().map(virtualRow => (
          <div key={virtualRow.key}
               style={{ position: 'absolute', top: virtualRow.start, height: virtualRow.size }}>
            <ListRow item={items[virtualRow.index]} />
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 8C. Backend Payload Trimming — Endpoint-Level Sparse Fieldsets

> **Addresses Codex ISSUE-11**: Generic `Schema::getColumnListing()` replaced with endpoint-specific allowlists to prevent exposing unintended columns or dropping columns needed by eager loading/serializers.

Add `?fields=` query parameter support with **per-resource allowlists**:

```php
// In each DomainService or Resource class, define allowed list fields:
// app/Services/V5/FeeCollection/InvoiceDomainService.php
const ALLOWED_LIST_FIELDS = [
    'id', 'invoice_code', 'contract_id', 'customer_id', 'status',
    'total_amount', 'paid_amount', 'due_date', 'issue_date', 'created_at',
];

// In V5DomainSupportService or QueryRequestSupport
public function applySparseFieldset(Builder $query, Request $request, array $allowedFields): Builder
{
    if ($fields = $request->query('fields')) {
        $requested = array_intersect(explode(',', $fields), $allowedFields);
        if (!empty($requested)) {
            // Always include id and fields required by eager loading
            $requested = array_unique(array_merge(['id'], $requested));
            $query->select($requested);
        }
    }
    return $query;
}
```

**Each endpoint must define its own allowlist** — no table-wide introspection. Allowlist must include all fields needed by:
- `toArray()` / Resource serialization (computed fields like `outstanding`)
- Eager loading foreign keys (`customer_id` for `->with('customer')`)
- Sorting columns (if sortable)

Frontend sends `?fields=id,invoice_code,status,total_amount,due_date` for list views instead of fetching all 20+ columns.

### 8D. Runtime Lazy Loading with React.lazy (addresses Codex ISSUE-8)

> Build-time chunking (8E below) alone does not guarantee deferred loading. `React.lazy()` + `Suspense` ensures chunks are loaded on-demand at runtime.

**Route-level lazy loading** (heaviest components loaded only when navigated to):
```typescript
// In router/routes.tsx or equivalent
const CustomerRequestHub = React.lazy(() => import('../components/customer-request/CustomerRequestManagementHub'));
const FeeCollectionHub = React.lazy(() => import('../components/fee-collection/FeeCollectionHub'));
const RevenueHub = React.lazy(() => import('../components/revenue-mgmt/RevenueManagementHub'));
const LeadershipDashboard = React.lazy(() => import('../components/customer-request/LeadershipDashboard'));

// Wrap with Suspense boundary
<Suspense fallback={<div className="flex justify-center p-8"><LoadingSpinner /></div>}>
  <CustomerRequestHub />
</Suspense>
```

**Modal-level lazy loading** (after P5E split, modals loaded when opened):
```typescript
// In components/modals/index.tsx
const ContractModal = React.lazy(() => import('./ContractModal'));
const InvoiceModal = React.lazy(() => import('./InvoiceModal'));
// ... each modal lazy-loaded
```

